overnments, the relative technical expertise of these governments and secretariat officials, the personalities of these officials. An original conclusion is reached: civil services, at least at the international level, do not necessarily play a significant policy-making role in their organizations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInternational agenciesxAdministration. 0aOrganisations internationalesxGestion. 0aPolicy sciences. 0aSciences de la politique. 0aSecretariatsxAdministration. 0aSecretariatsxGestion. 0aSecrétariatsxGestion. 4aPolitical Science: International Relations. 4aSocial Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920698440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206984423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206984/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles